criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Have a deficit in the areas of attention and/or memory.

          -  Have current cognitive deficits which were present from the time of the injury, are
             persistent, and are deemed to be the result of the brain injury;

          -  Be at least 12 months post brain injury;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  A history of a major brain surgery;

          -  A penetrating brain injury (e.g., gun shot wound);

          -  A current diagnosis of epilepsy;

          -  Had more than one seizure in the past year (patients who have had a single seizure
             within a year post-injury will be considered on a case by case basis);

          -  Previous exposure to rivastigmine.
